description: From Middle English papirus, borrowed from Latin papȳrus, from Ancient Greek πάπυρος (pápuros), of unknown origin. Doublet of paper.

nouns.description: papyrus (usually uncountable, plural papyri or papyruses)

entries.meaning: (usually uncountable) A plant (Cyperus papyrus) in the sedge family, native to the Nile river valley, paper reed.
(usually uncountable) A material similar to paper made from the papyrus plant.
(countable) A scroll or document written on papyrus.
